#: ../../Troubleshooting/Troubleshooting.rst:46
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The key insight was that the top two layers of sand stopped producing filter "
"water soon after beginning a filter run. A complete stoppage means that "
"clogging ISN'T the issue! Clogging would decrease the flow rate, but it "
"wouldn't stop flow because the clogging would have to be absolute to stop the "
"flow."
msgstr ""
"La clave fue que las dos capas superiores de arena dejaron de producir agua de "
"filtro poco después de comenzar una operación de filtrado. ¡Un paro completo "
"significa que la obstrucción no es el problema! La obstrucción disminuiría la "
"velocidad de flujo, pero no detendría el flujo porque la obstrucción tendría "
"que ser absoluta para detener el flujo."

#: ../../Troubleshooting/Troubleshooting.rst:48
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The failure was that the water traveling horizontally in the branches and trunk "
"carries air bubbles to the vertically downward flowing pipe (see a photo here). "
"The air accumulates in that pipe and the water falls through the air losing "
"energy like a waterfall. Water completely stops flowing through the layers of "
"the filter that exit through that trunk line when the height of the air is "
"equal to the available energy driving water through the StaRS filter."
msgstr ""
"El fallo fue que el agua que viajaba horizontalmente en las ramas y el tronco "
"lleva burbujas de aire al tubo que fluye verticalmente hacia abajo (ver una "
"foto aquí). El aire se acumula en ese tubo y el agua cae a través del aire "
"perdiendo energía como una cascada. El agua deja de fluir por completo a través "
"de las capas del filtro que salen por ese tronco cuando la altura del aire es "
"igual a la energía disponible que impulsa al agua a través del filtro StaRS."

#: ../../Troubleshooting/Troubleshooting.rst:50
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are two improvements required at El PODA. First, the transmission line "
"must be operated with downstream flow control to prevent air entrapment and "
"compression. That will likely be sufficient to solve the problem of air in the "
"filters. The second improvement is to add manual air release valves to the top "
"of each of the trunk lines so that operates can expel air during filtration. "
"Note that these air vents must have a valve that is closed during backwash "
"because the filter is under negative pressure during backwash and would suck "
"air into the filter through those vents if they were open."
msgstr ""
"Hay dos mejoras necesarias en El PODA. Primero, la línea de transmisión debe "
"funcionar con un control de flujo descendente para evitar el atrapamiento y la "
"compresión del aire. Eso probablemente será suficiente para resolver el "
"problema del aire en los filtros. La segunda mejora es añadir válvulas de "
"liberación de aire manual en la parte superior de cada una de las líneas "
"troncales para que los operadores puedan expulsar el aire durante la "
"filtración. Tenga en cuenta que estos respiraderos de aire deben tener una "
"válvula que esté cerrada durante el retrolavado porque el filtro está bajo "
"presión negativa durante el retrolavado y aspiraría aire al filtro a través de "
"esos respiraderos si estuvieran abiertos."

#: ../../Troubleshooting/Troubleshooting.rst:52
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"EStaRS with the wing inlets make a possible failure mode. At the end of the "
"backwash if the operator closes the valve in the siphon quickly, the water "
"pressure rises quickly inside the filter. When the water rises in the three "
"entry passages it is possible that the water carries the sand inside the "
"branches with wings. And once there is sand inside the pipes, this sand may "
"hinder the flow of water during the filter run."
msgstr ""
"EStaRS con las entradas de las alas hacen un posible modo de fallo. Al final "
